snippet.title: Lived Black Experience CommUnity Dialogue Project
snippet.description:
The Southside Community Association began hosting “The Lived Black Experience” (LBE) CommUnity Dialogues in June 2020 as a direct response to the BLM movement and the need to foster, grow and promote a climate of understanding, acceptance and civil dialogue around the systemic, root causes of racism, inequality, and hate. 

The LBE presentations are lived streamed from the Lived Black Experience Facebook page and include topic experts from all over the United States several times a month.

If you enjoy this LBE, consider helping us continue the work with a monetary donation. You can do so by going to this link https://paypal.me/SouthsideFlagstaff (please designate the Lived Black Experience CommUnity Dialogue Project).

The Southside Community Association is a nonprofit, 501 C3 organization and as such donations could be tax-deductible, please ask your tax professional for more information.
